text: Test Page for the Centmin Mod Nginx HTTP Server Centmin Mod Nginx Test Page This page is used to test the proper operation of the Centmin Mod based Nginx HTTP server after it has been If you can read this page, it means that the Nginx HTTP server installed at this site is working You can further boost your Centmin Mod LEMP stack performance by following configuration tips outlined in How to boost Centmin Mod LEMP stack performance guide . Disclaimer Centmin Mod is a free open source software for CentOS Linux that can be downloaded and installed by anybody and was installed on this server by a party end user with no relation to Centmin Centmin Mod has no control over and is not responsible for the content contained on this If you are a member of the general public: The fact that you are seeing this page indicates that the website you just visited is either experiencing problems, or is undergoing routine maintenance or has recently just been installed and not correctly configured If you would like to let the administrators of this website know that you ve seen this page instead of the page you expected, you should send them In general, mail sent to the name "webmaster" and directed to the website s domain should reach the appropriate For example, if you experienced problems while visiting , you should send to "webmaster@example.com". If you are the website administrator: After Centmin Mod install, follow the Getting Started Guide to setup your Centmin Mod LEMP web You may want to change this file located within directory usr local nginx html . Note that until you do so, people visiting your website will see this page, and not your To prevent this page from ever being used, replace this file ( ).

Most people know that the plastic waste problem is huge - so huge that it can feel There is lots of information about the problem, and some of it is Are those “compostable” plastics real or just greenwashed junk gunking up our recycling systems? Are all plastics bad? Is the plastic waste problem just too big for me to have any kind of impact? Achieving sustainability in the textile industry is equally Even "organic" fabrics can wreak havoc on the planet when they require tons of water to grow and chemicals to dye for commercial In developing Shiki Wrap, we chose a fabric derived from recycled plastic because: - A critical part of solving the plastic waste problem is creating market demand for recycled plastic products, ideally consumer products that will be used again and again - The manufacturing and dying process takes little to no water or harmful chemicals - Most importantly, the whole point of making a product is to solve a problem and spark joy for the The stretchiness and softness of Shiki Wrap makes it fun to touch and easy to wrap with – both critical elements in order for people to make the change from paper wrap to Shiki Wrap without compromising View this post on Instagram A post shared by Shiki Wrap (@shikiwrapusa) In addition to utilizing fabric derived from recycled plastic, we are exploring strategic partnerships that will allow us to "upcycle" deadstock fabric that

Is it to Outsource Medical Billing? Billing was handled by traditional medical Entrepreneurs, on the other hand, are increasingly offering billing services that might relieve you of the burden of dealing with your own Is the service worth the money, or would it be preferable to do things the traditional way? The evidence is clear: it is preferable to outsource medical billing than than handle it Let s have a look at a few of the reasons for Reasons to Outsource Lower Costs: Economies of scale are advantageous to medical billing As production businesses produce more units, the cost per unit A billing company handles many times as many billing claims as a private As a result, they can handle each bill for a fraction of what a solo practise would These savings could be passed on to your private practise via the billing Outsourcing your billing can help your company save a lot of Variablize Fixed Expenses: The pay of your personnel will be your biggest expense if you need to establish your own billing Whether business is slow or growing, you must pay their salaries, which is in other wor

Monarch butterflies are not only beautiful but represent mystery, symbolism and The Monarch undergoes a complete metamorphosis representing a spiritual rebirth, transformation, change, hope and The Monarch Triathlon will do the same thing for the athletes that train and compete in the event but it goes beyond The Monarch Triathlon represents the rebirth of the women who have battled It represents the transformation and change that they undergo during their diagnosis and Finally, the Monarch triathlon brings hope and life to the participants and their loved The Monarch Triathlon Medal We have designed the Monarch Medal to come to life and provide a keepsake for each The spinning design will make the monarch butterfly seem as if it is moving through life and showcasing its beauty for all to The SheStrong ribbon in the middle of the monarch butterfly is removable and can be worn on a necklace, bracelet, or This reminder can be with each finisher every day as a reminder that they can do the It’s a reminder to celebrate life the way they celebrated their finish at the Monarch What Can I Expect At The Monarch Triathlon? The Monarch Triathlon will be unlike any other triathlon you’ve participated in or read Our finish line will be a celebration of life for the participants and their Athletes will get to record a personal message before the The message can be a tribute to yourself or a loved one you have lost to Brandy Ramirez, Founder of SheStrong says, “I would make a tribute to I battled stage 3 cancer from I also lost my mother to cancer in , so I would dedicate my race in her ” The video board will show these messages providing inspiration and motivation for the This finish line will come to life as each athlete crosses under the arch and all hear why athletes are racing and how important it is to them to be a part of the Monarch Does The Monarch Triathlon Offer A Relay Division? The Monarch Triathlon offers a relay If you’re new to the sport or prefer to race with friends then we have an option for Put together a team of 2 or 3 members to race and don’t forget to come up with a creative team For more information on the relay team rules CLICK HERE . Mandala Cohort : Every Sunday, from 2–4 PM PT , we meet on Zoom with a This facilitator is a peer who’s been through our program, and is using a curriculum based on a workbook that we’ve published and we’ll be sending to Structure: Each session begins with a quick on how everyone is Then, our facilitator shares the norms for the day, as well as a small overview of the three We then spend the rest of the time blending in writing exercises, meditations, and structured sharing sessions where people examine their lives safely and in Community: Over the course of four weeks, bonds begin to form with other folks in the This is all based on our shared None of it is forced, but all of it is And if you’d like, at the end of the four weeks, you’re invited to join our community of advisors that are keen on growing the program into what it can ABOUT What is Mandala How We Work Why We Exist About Us © Mandala JOIN MANDALA Join the Cohort Join the Community Testimonials FAQ ​ CONTACT Schedule an Intro Call Email: Call: (650) ​ ​   FAQ | Mandala Mandala HOME ABOUT FAQ CONTACT More Use tab to navigate through the menu JOIN US Frequently Asked Questions How much does this cost? Anyone can join the Mandala community . It’s We host dinner groups, meditation sessions, and invite wellness experts to connect with And we also have cohorts where we work through a curriculum over the course of four In order to accommodate for varying financial needs, we provide a sliding scale for any fee between $15 hr and $40 hr ($150 to $400 for the month, with a requested price of $250). Those who can pay it forward can choose to do The fees go to accommodate for the facilitator’s time pay for the production and shipment of the Mandala workbook and some goodies and operation of the business Is this therapy? Therapy tends to be 1:1 and therapists are generally licensed practitioners by their They have undergone supervision, training and are able to handle a range of Mandala’s facilitators are all And while our curriculum has been developed in partnership and under the counsel of therapists, psychologists, registered nurses and medical professionals, what we offer either supplements the services of a 1:1 therapy or helps provide help to those who therapy does not Can I become a facilitator? Joining a cohort is the first step, and then you undergo three steps: (1) undergo training to facilitate, led by both an existing facilitator and a clinician (2) host a community wide event and practice holding space (3) a cohort, with the supervision of an existing Why focus on people of color, when everyone could benefit? We believe there’s incredible value in solidarity, and tapping into shared experiences . Support groups in schools or workplaces are a testament to And more importantly focusing on the needs of one population will help us get more creative and imagine what sorts of services would help If you d like to chat to learn more, feel free to schedule a free SCHEDULE A CALL ABOUT What is Mandala How We Work Why We Exist About Us © Mandala JOIN MANDALA Join the Cohort Join the Community Testimonials FAQ ​ CONTACT Schedule an Intro Call Email: Call: (650) ​ ​   About Us | Mandala: Emotional Wellbeing for People of Color Mandala HOME ABOUT FAQ CONTACT More Use tab to navigate through the menu JOIN US Who We Are We’re a group of people — students, parents, artists, journalists, mental health providers, nurses, All committed to the mission of emotional Why Do We Exist? Maconnell James Parkman Mac Parkman was a vibrant human being who embodied the best attributes that humanity and God find endearing in this Warm, funny, witty, kind, compassionate, calm, loyal, caring is just a few of the characteristics that can describe this wonderful young He brought so much warmth and sunshine to everyone he touched, yet was as tough a competitor as one could be….a true peaceful warrior until he left this Mac was born on March , , in Albuquerque, NM to a loving, mixed family and spent his first 6 years there growing up in the foothills to the west of the city in Tijeras, As the “new” kid, his mom and sisters welcomed warmly him while his father was overseas, taking part in the invasion of As a newly knit family that had never raised a son or brother, he brought so much love into their lives and brought them closer together with his presence, a gift that the family shares to this Mac was a quiet boy, always wanting to do things, and he was physically active from the Track, baseball, karate, and skiing with his dad were his early activities, and he loved being active and with his friends, especially as they would all eat out in great places like Blakes, Sadie’s, and Hooters He was quick to learn, was active all the time, and enjoyed an early introduction to God at the local Prince of Peace school where he was loved by teachers and students alike, except for a short period where he tackled the other In , Mac moved to Woodland Park with his family and enrolled in Colorado Springs Christian School He lived on a ranch, surrounded by forests, and became part of the wrestling team in first grade, along with almost the entire Mac was one of the few kids to stay with wrestling and loved the sport and the camaraderie and continued participation until his Mac had several very close friends, two of them Nathan and Parker that would attend “cookie church” with him, as the local Methodist church had a very elderly congregation that loved to He loved having his friends over to play games, jump on the trampoline, shoot air guns (or real guns on his dad’s range), play tag, camp out and we could hear them wrestling and bumping around upstairs well into the Because of his father’s business activities, Mac fell in love with new places and was always on planes, with his dad and family going all over the and the Everywhere he went, he would always want to experience the local culture, food, and He visited Costa Rica, the Hawaiian Islands, Egypt, Finland, Australia, New Zealand, Tahiti, the UAE, he rode camels and entered the Great Pyramids, hiked mountains and glaciers, went zip lining, kayaking, scuba diving, snorkeling, even went skiing in the UAE in an indoor ski simulator and practiced skydiving in an indoor skydiving He was always interested in what was going on and had a thirst for adventure that never, ever left Mac was also a very active video gamer and loved to game with his friends both and Over the years it became one of his outlets to take part in Competition and gaming were very important to He developed a group of friends who competed together and some of the best memories we have of Mac would be his whooping and yelling with his friends while they took part in Apex, Brawlhalla, and Grand Theft Mac’s Love of Sports But it was sports that defined who Mac was in his later While we knew he loved wrestling, Mac approached us about joining the football team in Of course, they encouraged him to be and do what he wanted to do, so he joined the CSCS middle school With wrestling and now football, the family became used to a new, active traveling routine that stretched over months of the year, supporting practices, team dinners, and taking Mac to We thoroughly relished every minute that Mac was engaged in sports, as we always wanted to support him in doing the things he Mac continued this schedule all the way till the end of

Well, what if we told you that it’s not only possible, it would actually make money in the It’s simply about giving money to people who need Seed money grants set at the federal poverty guidelines (FPGs) will end financial The economic costs of childhood poverty alone are $1 Trillion a year, and an estimated ,000 people a year die from poverty in the United If we provide seed money to every American and simply tax back that income for those already well above the FPGs, the net cost for eradicating poverty drops to below $200Bn. That is an annual return of $800Bn. Over years, these seed money grants would generate a return of over $8 Trillion, save Million lives, and lift million Americans out of We are paying trillions of dollars to keep people in This must Social programs provide the poor with benefits rather than cash, preventing them from voting with their wallets as full citizens in Many welfare programs for the poor also have income cutoffs, disincentivizing the poor from earning more when they are close to benefit Because these grants would be unconditional, it avoids perpetuating this “welfare trap,” allowing those who need it the most the agency to make their own financial How does that make money? The number of households below the poverty line multiplied by their average amount below the poverty line is $155Bn. To put that in context, the government collected $3.5Tn in taxes and spent $732Bn on the military in Yet $155Bn per year can nearly eliminate the ~$1Tn cost of childhood poverty, as well as streamline the $242Bn spent on all our social Spending just $155Bn per year can save us $1.24Tn per year, a % return, and that is without touching any healthcare spending and leaving several other social programs in Two Journeys Across America - A Watch the latest conversation between Darryl Finkton, Jr and the renowned writer and journalist James WATCH THE LATEST Interested i

LinkedIn Twitter Youtube Medium OUR MISSION Advance equality in medical education OUR MISSION To connect medical students, graduates and physicians to collectively advance equality in medical education, THE CHALLENGE Every international medical graduate’s journey to become a physician is unique and their personal sacrifice and perseverance is Although aspiring physicians share the same end goal, they all don’t start their journey on equal Most international medical students face geographic, and educational inequities that make their journey that much more The consequence of these inequalities directly contributes to the global physician shortage and ultimately, the quality of care provided to patient populations As the global community focuses on addressing a spectrum of social determinants of health at a governmental level, the opportunity to effect change in health outcomes begins by providing every medical student equal access to medical education resources and Project IMG is on a mission to connect medical students, graduates and physicians to collectively advance equality in medical education, As a collective of learners and educators, we provide an ecosystem that guides and equips students throughout their medical education By combining free, curated medical education programs with a peer support structure, we enable every student an opportunity to advance their academic ORGANIZATIONAL GOALS Goal 1 Equal access and inclusion Our goal is to provide every student equal and free access to medical education resources and opportunities provided by our collective of students and Goal 2 Equal treatment Every student interaction within our collective should be accepting, valuing, respectful, supportive, safe and Our members should feel challenged to be invested in the pursuits of learning and excellence without fear of threat, humiliation, danger or Goal 3 Equal opportunity to learn Our goal is to ensure that every member, regardless of their characteristics and background, is presented an opportunity to reach high standards of Goal 4 Equal resources We recognize that not all students have all the resources needed to complete their As a collective, we will work with donors and other partners to distribute resources in ways to ensure that all members achieve high academic MENU MENU Membership About Us Programs Application Contact Us trainML - Training Jobs Features Solutions Pricing Documentation Login Sign-up Serverless Deep Learning Training Jobs trainML Training Jobs allow you to effortlessly run parallel model training experiments across dozens of Train Models without Servers servers tend to suffer from the twin problems of utilization and Due to their significant expense, companies want to ensure their servers are being maximally Every minute the GPU is idle is a waste of their On the , when a server is maximally utilized, processes must be implemented to schedule training experiments between users, frequently wasting even more expensive data scientist cloud instances seek to ameliorate this problem, but come with their own They are dramatically more expensive than normal CPU Instance setup (loading model code and datasets) and teardown (copying artifacts and other data to permanent storage) can consume a significant amount of time (and cost). Forgetting to stop the instances after training completes can be a very costly trainML Training Jobs are the best of All you have to do is provide the git URL for the model code, create or select a dataset to run the training on, specify where you want the model artifacts to be sent, and the command to execute the training trainML automatically downloads the required inputs, runs your training script, uploads the results, and terminates itself when it s With our cloud infrastructure, you never have to worry about utilization or Scale Out Parallel Experiments with Ease Frequently, customers want to compare the results of different model architectures or different sets of hyperparameters on the same Using a single server, you would have to wait until each training run finished to being the next experiment, wasting valuable If you run each experiment on a separate server, you would have to incur the setup and teardown costs many more With trainML Training Jobs, scaling an experiment to run multiple workers in parallel as simple as adding more workers to the training You can then specify a command with different command line arguments for each worker, but reuse the same model and If you re using an optimization library like hyperopt, you can use the same command for each worker and let the framework do the You can find an example this here . Monitor Experiments Centrally A significant challenge with running multiple training experiments in parallel is monitoring their The trainML platform captures and centralizes the log output of all workers running an You can view output in for all workers simultaneously, or filter down to watch each worker By monitoring their progress, you can easily detect if you need to stop a worker early and save your money for more productive Get Results Directly on Your Laptop trainML Training Jobs can automatically upload their results to cloud storage providers for permanent However, customer usually prefer to analyze the results of a training job in their local environment In this case, you can use the local storage option to allow the training job s workers to upload their results directly to your local This advanced function requires the use of the trainML local connection capability, so ensure you satisfy the prerequisites before attempting to use the local data Read about the process for starting and monitoring a trainML Training Learn More Get started creating a trainML Training Job Try It Now Use a simple image classification tutorial to familiarize yourself with training Learn More Find out more about instance and storage billing and credits Learn More Home Documentation Privacy Policy Terms Of Use Â© trainML, LLC, All rights reserved   trainML -
